Former Governor of Illinois Rod Blagojevich arrives at a US federal prison in Colorado to begin a 14 year sentence on corruption charges. (Reuters)Channel 4 news anchor Jon Snow tells the Leveson Inquiry that Associated Newspapers, which publishes the Daily Mail and Mail on Sunday, is worse than News International's titles, that it has a "pernicious" and sometimes "mendacious" agenda to undermine people in public life, and predicts that "very possibly they will go after me for saying so". (The Guardian)